  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Life-saving Assistance to Vulnerable Women and Children Malian Refugees in Agando and Chinwaren</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Objective 1: Assure the short and medium term food security and nutrition of women and children in the Agando and Chinwaren sites

Activity 1.1. Provide 300 women with cash for work

Activity 1.2. Provide 908 women with training in revenue-generating activities



Objective 2: Improve the health and hygiene services currently provided at the Agando and Chinwaren sites

Activity 2.1. Reconstruct the health clinic at Agando to provide maternal health facilities

Activity 2.2. Provide essential medicines, supplies and equipments to improve health services

Activity 2.3. Provide sensitization and training activities to increase population awareness of RH and other health issues as well as water-borne diseases and malaria



Objective 3: Provide emergency shelter for refugee families with children at Agando and Chinwaren sites

Activity 3.1. Distribute to 1500 households a shelter kit whose design is durable, rain and wind-resistant and culturally appropriate</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">RI is filling immediate gaps in humanitarian assistance by improving the food security, health and shelter of Malian refugees, especially vulnerable women and children, in the Agando and Chinwaren sites of Tahoua province.</narrative>
  </description>
